KEYBOARD FOR XIAOMI
PRIVACY NOTICE
1.
OUR
                APPROACH TO PRIVACY
1.1
ekatoX
Singapore Private Limited
,
137
Telok
Ayer Street, #08-01, Singapore 068602
("
ekatoX
", "
we
", "
our
" or "
us
") is committed to respecting your privacy. This
                privacy notice sets out how we collect, store, process, transfer, share and use information that
                identifies or is associated with you ("
personal information
")
1.2
EkatoX
operates
a service, which we make available
                through an application available for download on your device (the "
Keyboard for Xiaomi
App
"), that allows you to create customised keyboards on
                your device (your "
Keyboard for Xiaomi
"), and to send emojis, stickers and GIFs (the
                "
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
Service
").
1.3
This privacy notice applies to the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service. Please ensure that you have read and understood
                this privacy notice
before
accessing or using the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service.
2.
WHO IS
                RESPONSIBLE FOR THE USE OF YOUR PERSONAL
INFORMATION
EkatoX
may
use proprietary software licensed to it by
                third party entities for the purpose of collecting and processing your personal information.  As a
                result of the use of such software, your personal information may also be collected by Facebook, Google,
Appsflyer
and Paytm.
EkatoX
is
the controller of the personal information
                we hold about you in connection with your use of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service. This means that we determine and are responsible
                for how your personal information is used.
3.
HOw WE
                Process Personal Information and on Which BAsis
3.1
How we process personal data depends on how you
                interact with us and which functionalities you decide to use. This means that we may process the
                following data:
(a)
Your
                    transaction history.
If you subscribe to any of the VIP Features or purchase
special skin types in Keyboard for Xiaomi, we will be informed by the payment service 
                    provider that you have paid for this service of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service. We will not collect any of your bank account information, bank card information nor any other financial information.
(b)
Information you submit into the search fields,
for example, the search service on the keyboard using the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
. In order to offer the most relevant results to you, we will 
                collect words and phrases that you enter into the search fields.
(c)
If you choose a personalised theme for your
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
. If you choose a personalised theme for the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
and upload to the platform of the Keyboard for Xiaomi, we will process information such as the background picture, text colour, 
                    font and any custom skins or other features that you choose for your Keyboard for Xiaomi.
(d)
Your preferences and
                settings
.
We may collect information
such as your settings regarding data sharing, the use of
                specific functions (including the Key Sounds function), and the level of access that you grant
EkatoX
to
your device.
(e)
Information collected from third
                party social media companies
. If you connect to your Keyboard for Xiaomi account by logging in to your social media account, 
                we will access information your username and profile image, in accordance with, and only if permitted by, your privacy settings on that social network.
(f)
Information collected from third
                party apps, such as
third
                party
app development and
                analytics platforms
. We may collect information
                from third party apps. This information may include your IP address, statistics regarding your use of
                the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
and
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service and any crashes or problems experienced while using
                the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
and
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service
.
(g)
Usage information collected
                automatically.
We may collect usage information
                automatically.
For example, information about
                your device and its software and about the way you use the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service and
Keyboard for Xiaomi
, such as the type of device, physical dimension, division
                ration, CPU type, memory capacity, operating system version, version of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service and
Keyboard for Xiaomi
, keyboard type and typing performance when using the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service and
Keyboard for Xiaomi
, crash information (such as defects that occurred), and
                unique ID for each
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
.
3.2
We provide you with an option to opt-out from many
                of these functions via the settings of either your device (camera and microphone use) or the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
App. If you opt-out, we will be no longer able to access
                the personal data relating to the part of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service that you opted-out from. However, please note that
                if you opt-out we will also no longer be able to provide you with that part of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service.
When you exercise your option to opt-out from any of these
                functions by toggling a feature ‘off’ in the settings, a written communication on your behalf will
                automatically be sent to
EkatoX
and
will be constituted as withdrawal of
                consent from sharing the corresponding information necessary for the functionality. You may start using
                the functions again by toggling the feature ‘on’ in the settings, which will automatically send a
                written communication on your behalf to
EkatoX
and
will be constituted as express consent for
                collection and use of the data required for the functionality as per the terms of this Privacy Notice
                and the Terms of Use.
3.3
The table in the
Annex
sets out more information about what personal information
                may be transferred to
EkatoX
and
the purposes and lawful bases for such
                transfers.
3.4
We may anonymise and aggregate any of the personal
                information we collect (so that we can no longer identify you, directly or indirectly). We may use
                anonymised information for purposes that include testing our IT systems, research, data analysis,
                improving the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service and developing new products and features. We may
                also share such anonymised and aggregated information with others.
4.
How
                long we will store your personal information
4.1
We will usually store the personal information we
                collect about you for no longer than necessary for the purposes set out in the
Annex
, including for the purposes of our legitimate business
                interests and in satisfying any legal or reporting requirements.
4.2
To determine the appropriate retention period for
                personal information, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal information, the
                potential risk of harm from unauthorised use or disclosure of your personal information, the purposes
                for which we process your personal information and the applicable legal requirements.
5.
RECIPIENTS
                    OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
We may share your personal information with the following
                (as required in accordance with the purposes set out in the
Annex
):
(a)
Our affiliates
. We may share personal information with
                other entities owned by or under common ownership with
EkatoX
to
provide, develop and improve the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Services and to determine products and
                services that may be of interest to you.
(b)
Service providers and
                advisors
. We may share your personal
                information with third party vendors and other service providers. In particular, such services may
                include professional services, such as legal and accounting services, payment processing, mailing, email
                or chat services, fraud prevention, web hosting, or analytic services. Any such service providers will –
                by appropriate data processing agreements – be bound only to process personal information on our behalf
                and under our instructions, unless such service providers act as independent or joint
                controllers.
(c)
Purchasers and third parties in
                connection with a business transaction
. Your
                personal information may be disclosed to third parties in connection with a transaction, such as a
                merger, asset or share sale, reorganisation, financing, change of control or acquisition of all or a
                part of our business, in addition to bankruptcy, liquidation and similar actions. In such cases we
may transfer or
disclose your personal information to the limited extent
                necessary to the applicable third party.
(d)
Law enforcement, regulators and
                other parties for legal reasons
. We may share
                your personal information with third parties as required by law or if we reasonably believe that such
                action is necessary: (
i
) to comply with the law, or to comply with the reasonable
                requests of law enforcement and other government agencies; (ii) to detect and investigate illegal
                activities and breaches of agreements, including our Terms of Service (iii) to
protect the security or integrity of our
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service
; and/or (iv) to exercise or protect the claims, rights and
                property of
EkatoX
,
                or the rights, property or personal safety of its users or others.
(e)
Otherwise with
                consent.
We may disclose your personal
                information to certain other third parties with your explicit
consent
.
6.
STORING AND TRANSFERRING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
6.1
Storage of Data, Security and Transfers
. We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal information against accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, and unauthorised disclosure or access. All data that we collect, both personal information and non-personal information,
                will be stored by our cloud hosting provider on secure servers in India. All data that we collect is stored in data centres hosted by Amazon India located in India, with their corporate address at The Capital, 
                Plot No. C-70, G-Block, 7th Floor, Bandra Kurla Complex, Bandra East, Mumbai 400051. Please note that although we implement and ensure reasonable measures to protect your personal information, no websites, internet transmissions, 
                computer systems or wireless connections are absolutely secure. We will never send you unsolicited emails or contact you by phone requesting your account ID, password, credit or debit card information or national identification numbers.
                Some non-personal information we collect may be transferred to and processed in countries outside of the India, namely to counties where we and/or our third-party service providers have operations. By using the Keyboard for Xiaomi Service and agreeing to the terms of use and this privacy notice,
                you hereby consent to such transfer of data. In the event of such a transfer, please note that different countries or regions may offer different levels of data protection. We will take measures to ensure that the data we collect is processed in accordance with this privacy notice and applicable laws.
                This means that we will ensure that: (i) data is transferred to countries recognised as offering an equivalent level of protection as compared to the level of protection in the country you are located; and (ii) the transfer is made pursuant to appropriate safeguards, and the information is processed 
                and stored as per the reasonable security practices and procedures mandated by the Information Technology (Reasonable Security Practices and Procedures and Sensitive Personal Data or Information) Rules, 2011 or any other law pertaining to protection of data in force in India at the relevant time.
6.2
If you wish to enquire further about the safeguards used, please contact us using the details set out at the end of this privacy notice.
7.
your
                rights in respect of your personal information
7.1
In accordance with applicable privacy law, you have
                the following rights in respect of your personal information that we hold:
(a)
Right of consent or refusal to
                give consent
: Before we start collecting your
                personal information, you have the right to refuse to grant us consent.  We shall collect your
                personal information only upon receiving express consent in writing from you.  You can give your
                consent for our collection and processing of your personal information upon clicking the ‘I Agree’
                option, which is made with this Privacy Policy. Similarly, you may choose to refuse to give your consent
                upon clicking the ‘I Refuse’ option, which is made available with this Privacy Policy.  You
                understand that once you click on the ‘I Agree’ option, this will amount to you granting us your consent
                in writing, for the collection and usage of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy
                Policy.
(b)
Right of access
. You have the right to obtain access to your personal
                information. This includes the right to obtain:
(i)
confirmation of whether we are processing your
                personal information;
(ii)
information about the categories of personal
                information we are processing, the purposes for which we process your personal information and
                information as to how we determine applicable retention periods;
(iii)
information about the categories of recipients with
                whom we may share your personal information and if those recipients are located in third countries;
                and
(iv)
a copy of the personal information we hold about
                you.
(c)
Right of portability
. You have the right, in certain circumstances, to receive a
                copy of the personal information you have provided to us in a structured, commonly used,
                machine-readable format that supports re-use, or to request the transfer of your personal information to
                another person.
(d)
Right to
                rectification
. You have the right to obtain
                rectification of any inaccurate or incomplete personal information we hold about you without undue
                delay.
However,
                    you understand and agree that we do not hold any responsibility towards
the accuracy or authenticity of the user data which you
                    have submitted or we have collected through your use of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
service.
(e)
Right to erasure
. You have the right to require us to erase your personal
                information without undue delay if the continued processing of that personal information is not
                justified.
(f)
Right to restriction
. You have the right to require us to limit the purposes for
                which we process your personal information
(for
                example, where the accuracy of the personal data is contested by you), for a period of time that enables
                us to verify the accuracy of that personal data.
(g)
RIGHT TO OBJECT
. You also have the right to object to
                any processing based on our legitimate interests, at any time, where your objection is raised on grounds
                relating to your particular situation.
Should you decide to object to the
                processing of your personal data, we will stop processing personal data concerning you, unless we can
                demonstrate compelling reasons for continuing to process your personal data that override your
                interests, rights and freedoms, or where we process your personal data to establish, exercise, or defend
                our legal claims. You can object to direct marketing activities for any reason at any time.
(h)
Right to withdraw
                consent
. We do not need
                your consent for all of the processing activities we undertake. However, if we rely on your consent as
                the lawful basis for our processing (as identified in the
Annex
), and you have provided such consent
                for the processing of your personal information, you have the right to withdraw your consent at any
                time. If you withdraw your consent this will not affect the lawfulness of our use of your personal
                information before your withdrawal. You can withdraw your consent to the processing of your personal
                information, the basis of which is set out in the
Annex,
by updating your settings of your
                device (camera and microphone use) and prohibiting any further collection or processing of your personal
                data or in
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
App
, by following
                    the process laid down in Clause 3.2 of this Privacy Notice.
If you withdraw your consent, we may no
                longer be able to provide you with the corresponding feature of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service, except in the cases where you
                make use of the opt-out option as explained above under "Personal information processed locally by
                the
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
Service on your
                device".
7.2
If you wish to exercise one of
                these rights, please contact us using the contact details at the end of this privacy notice.
7.3
Due to the confidential nature of data processing
                we may ask you to provide proof of identity when exercising the above rights.
7.4
Right to lodge a
                complaint
. You also have
                the right to lodge a complaint to a competent data protection authority. If you are based in the
                European Union, information about how to contact your local data protection authority is available
here
. If you are based in the United
                Kingdom, your local data protection authority is the Information Commissioner's Office, which can be
                contacted
here
.
8.
Interest-Based
                    Advertising
8.1
We participate in
                interest-based advertising and use third party advertising companies to serve you targeted
                advertisements based on your browsing history and use of the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service. We may share, or we may permit
                the following
third
                party
online advertising
                networks, social media companies and other third party services, to collect information about your use
                of the
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
Service (in accordance with their own policies regarding privacy which you can access below) over time so
                that they may play or display ads on other websites, apps or services you may use (including Facebook),
                and on other devices you may use. A list of entities apart from
EkatoX
who
may collect your information is
                provided below:
(i)
Facebook, Inc. (
to access Facebook’s privacy policy click here
)
(ii)
Google, Inc. (
to access Google’s privacy policy click here
)
(iii)
Appsflyer
, Ltd. (
to access Appsflyer’s privacy policy click here
)
(iv)
One97 Communications, Ltd. (“Paytm”) (
to access Paytm’s privacy policy click here
)
8.2
These third parties may collect
                (or we may share) mobile identifiers such as your Google Advertising ID, as well as your device's IP
                address, information about other applications on your device, your location, information about your use
                of the
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
Service, 
                and information about which advertisements you have seen or clicked on.
8.3
We and our third-party partners mentioned above
                use this information to make the advertisements you see online more relevant to your interests, as well
                as to provide advertising-related services such as reporting, attribution, analytics and market research.
8.4
We and our third-party partners
                may also link your various devices so that content you see on one device can result in relevant
                advertising on another device. We do this by collecting information about each device you use when you
                are logged in to the
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service on that device. We may also
                work with third party partners who employ tracking technologies, or the application of statistical
                modelling tools, to determine if two or more devices are linked to a single user or household. We may
                share a common account identifier (such as a user ID) with third party advertising partners to help
                recognise you across devices. We and our partners can use this cross-device linkage to serve
                interest-based advertising and other personalised content to you across your devices, to perform
                analytics and to measure the performance of our advertising campaigns.
8.5
You may be able to limit the use of these
                identifiers for interest-based advertising on a particular device through the settings on your device,
                by selecting "limit ad tracking" (iOS) or "opt out of interest based ads" (Android).
                You may also be able to opt-out of some, but not all, interest-based ads served by mobile ad networks by
                visiting
http://youradchoices.com/appchoices
and downloading the mobile
AppChoices
app.
8.6
To learn more about interest-based advertising and
                how you may be able to opt-out of some of this advertising, you may wish to visit:
(a)
the Network Advertising Initiative’s
                ("
NAI
") online resources, at
http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices
;
(b)
the Digital Advertising Alliance’s
                ("
DAA
") resources at
www.aboutads.info/choices
; and/or
(c)
Your Online Choices at
www.youronlinechoices.eu
.
8.7
Please note that opting-out of receiving
                interest-based advertising through online resources from the NAI, DAA or Your Online Choices will only
                opt you out from receiving interest-based ads on that specific browser or device, but you may still
                receive interest-based ads on your other devices. You would need to perform the opt-out on each browser
                or device that you use.
8.8
Some of these opt-outs may not be effective unless
                your browser is set to accept cookies. If you delete cookies, change your browser settings, switch
                browsers or devices, or use another operating system, you will need to opt-out again.
8.9
Please note that opting out of interest-based
                advertising does not mean you will no longer see advertising on your device – it just means that adverts
                may no longer be tailored to your interests.
9.
LINKS
                TO THIRD PARTY SITES
The
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service may, from time to time, contain links to and from
                third party websites, including those of other users, our partner networks, advertisers, partner
                merchants, news publications, retailers and affiliates. If you follow a link to any of these websites,
                please note that these websites have their own privacy notices and that we do not accept any
                responsibility or liability for their policies. Please check the individual policies before you submit
                any information to those websites.
10.
OUR
                POLICY TOWARDS CHILDREN
The
Keyboard for Xiaomi
Service is not directly offered to any child as defined by applicable laws and regulations of each jurisdiction (a “Child” or “Children”). We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from Children. In the event that we learn that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a Child, we will delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any information from a Child, please contact us using the details at the end of the privacy notice.
11.
CHANGES
                TO THIS PRIVACY NOTICE
We may update this privacy notice from time to time, and you
                should review this page periodically. When we change this privacy notice, we will
                update the "last modified" date at the end of this privacy notice. Changes to this privacy
                notice are effective when they are posted on this page.
12.
NOTICE
                TO YOU
If we need to provide you with information about something,
                whether for legal, marketing or other business-related purposes, we will select what we believe is the
                lawful and most effective way to get in contact with you. We will usually do this through email or by
                placing a notice on the
Keyboard for
                Xiaomi
Service. The fact that we may send
                notices to you will not stop you from being able to opt-out of certain types of contact as described in
                this privacy notice.
